HEADWORD: Octofid
<hw>Oc"to*fid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Octo-</ets> +
root of L. <ets>findere</ets> to split: cf. F.
<ets>octofide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Cleft or separated
into eight segments, as a calyx.</def>⟦br⟧
